ervices and basically shove your hard earned money into your face cause it isn't enough.<br><br>Ports i can see costing money, it takes alot of mana and the wiz/druids time to port someone somewhere.  Rezes? sure lots of mana and time used up for them - fair amount of money is expected to be given out.  But what do you need 20pp+for, for a spell that would barely move the casters mana, require no movement or grouping whatsoever, and after that said they would do it.<br><br>What is that 20pp covering? 10 second of opening a spell book? well if we are going by a charge of 20pp for every 10 seconds of time used up let me start charging 3kpp for a rez.<br><br>This wasn't a rant intended to get everyone mad at me, guess it was my mistake to assume finding alot of people including myself who are kind enough to port/rez for free or kindly accept any donation equal to what the person of said level is able to donate  are commonplace.  For a level 33 still in patchwork and raw-hide - 20pp is quite alot for me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uorakkus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orakkus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#330000>(4/15/02 3:12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=498.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pages.prodigy.net/ivan02/EQPic/Sigpic/sigpic_04.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: People who rip you off with TLs/Gates</span><hr size=1> Dyaraeen, the going charge IS a factor.  If he was greedy he'd demand something like 100pp or something.  20pp for his trouble, nothing out of the ordinary.  Yeah, I'll agree with ya that if he said he was going to do it that he should have said his price up front, but that's the only thing I can agree with you on.<br><br>I'm still having a hard time believing that you've played a high-level wizard, either that or your other server must be filled with graduates of the Mr. Rodgers class of niceness.  While I don't mind doing TLs all that much, for every one I do in a public area, there magically spawns 4 or 5 tells asking for TLs (and if I get any stupid tells like "D00d, I need a TL, pls thx", I will personally escort them to the my summer retreat in Skyfire.. and THERE ARE NO TLs TO Emerald Jungle!  STOP ASKING FOR THEM!).  So that 10 seconds of TL usually turns into a few minutes of dealing with TL beggers.<br><br>But remember what you said:<br><br>"Im fairly new to the server, but is this something i need to get used to on MM? My other server doesn't seem to have as many greedy people who try to rip you off."<br><br>Off of ONE encounter you derived this.  Here are the other encounters you listed:<br><br>"the couple times i have gotten a Trans the person gave them for free or were very happy with the donation is was able to give. "<br><br>But now all of MM is greedy?  Um... sure, whatever.  Then you give us this lovely bit:<br><br>"..guess it was my mistake to assume finding alot of people including myself who are kind enough to port/rez for free or kindly accept any donation equal to what the person of said level is able to donate are commonplace."<br><br>You found one that plays a certain way, which you didn't like, and to a certain extent I can agree with why you might be ticked off.  But going on a tie-rant about how evil all of MM is will surely get you properly flamed.  They are commonplace, you just didn't find one.   <p><b>Orakkus Mu'hadeeb</b><br><i>Evoker of the 56th Circle of Burning Hellice</i><br>Adventuring for the Triad of Honor.<br><br>Wizards may not be welcomed in groups.. but we are always welcomed at parties.  Why?  Because we do the